==English==
===Etymology===
[[Calque]] of Thai [[ไข่ลูกเขย]] ''(khai luuk kheeuy),'' from [[ไข่]] ''(khai,'' [[egg]]) + [[ลูกเขย]] ''(luuk kheeuy,'' [[son-in-law]]).

===Noun===
'''son-in-law egg''' ''(plural:'' '''[[son-in-law eggs]]''')
# A [[boiled egg]] that has been [[shell]]ed and then deep-fried.

===Synonyms=== 
* [[kai leuk koey]] (variously spelled; a Romanization of the Thai term)
